Arn.Description: Destination arn. Returned after successful create.

RoleArn.Description: AWS role ARN that grants access

Tags.Description: A list of key-value pairs that contain metadata for the destination.

Arn.Description: FUOTA task arn. Returned after successful create.

AssociateMulticastGroup.Description: Multicast group to associate. Only for update request.

AssociateWirelessDevice.Description: Wireless device to associate. Only for update request.

DisassociateMulticastGroup.Description: Multicast group to disassociate. Only for update request.

DisassociateWirelessDevice.Description: Wireless device to disassociate. Only for update request.

FirmwareUpdateImage.Description: FUOTA task firmware update image binary S3 link

FirmwareUpdateRole.Description: FUOTA task firmware IAM role for reading S3

FuotaTaskStatus.Description: FUOTA task status. Returned after successful read.

Id.Description: FUOTA task id. Returned after successful create.

Tags.Description: A list of key-value pairs that contain metadata for the FUOTA task.

NumberOfDevicesInGroup.Description: Multicast group number of devices in group. Returned after successful read.

NumberOfDevicesRequested.Description: Multicast group number of devices requested. Returned after successful read.

Arn.Description: Multicast group arn. Returned after successful create.

AssociateWirelessDevice.Description: Wireless device to associate. Only for update request.

DisassociateWirelessDevice.Description: Wireless device to disassociate. Only for update request.

Id.Description: Multicast group id. Returned after successful create.

Status.Description: Multicast group status. Returned after successful read.

Tags.Description: A list of key-value pairs that contain metadata for the Multicast group.

Key.Description: The key name of the tag. You can specify a value that is 1 to 128 Unicode characters in length and cannot be prefixed with aws:. You can use any of the following characters: the set of Unicode letters, digits, whitespace, _, ., /, =, +, and -.

Value.Description: The value for the tag. You can specify a value that is 0 to 256 Unicode characters in length and cannot be prefixed with aws:. You can use any of the following characters: the set of Unicode letters, digits, whitespace, _, ., /, =, +, and -.

Arn.Description: Arn for network analyzer configuration, Returned upon successful create.

Description.Description: The description of the new resource

Name.Description: Name of the network analyzer configuration

Tags.Description: An array of key-value pairs to apply to this resource.

TraceContent.Description: Trace content for your wireless gateway and wireless device resources

WirelessDevices.Description: List of wireless gateway resources that have been added to the network analyzer configuration

WirelessGateways.Description: List of wireless gateway resources that have been added to the network analyzer configuration

Arn.Description: Wireless device arn. Returned after successful create.

Id.Description: Wireless device Id. Returned after successful create.

LastUplinkReceivedAt.Description: The date and time when the most recent uplink was received.

LoRaWAN.Description: The combination of Package, Station and Model which represents the version of the LoRaWAN Wireless Device.

Tags.Description: A list of key-value pairs that contain metadata for the device. Currently not supported, will not create if tags are passed.

ThingArn.Description: Thing arn. Passed into update to associate Thing with Wireless device.

ThingName.Description: Thing Arn. If there is a Thing created, this can be returned with a Get call.

Type.Description: Wireless device type, currently only Sidewalk and LoRa

Arn.Description: Arn for Wireless Gateway. Returned upon successful create.

Id.Description: Id for Wireless Gateway. Returned upon successful create.

LastUplinkReceivedAt.Description: The date and time when the most recent uplink was received.

LoRaWAN.Description: The combination of Package, Station and Model which represents the version of the LoRaWAN Wireless Gateway.

Tags.Description: A list of key-value pairs that contain metadata for the gateway.

ThingArn.Description: Thing Arn. Passed into Update to associate a Thing with the Wireless Gateway.

ThingName.Description: Thing Name. If there is a Thing created, this can be returned with a Get call.
